SIMPLE: unconscionable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unconscionable
<hw>Un*con"scion*a*ble</hw>
<pr>(⟦ucr⟧n*k⟦ocr⟧n"sh⟦ucr⟧n*⟦adot⟧*b'l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Not conscionable; exceeding the limits of any reasonable claim or
expectation; not conforming to reason; unreasonable; inordinate;
extravagant; <as>as, an <ex>unconscionable</ex> person or demand;
<ex>unconscionable</ex> size.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Which use of reason, most reasonless and
<qex>unconscionable</qex>, is the utmost that any tyrant ever
pretended.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His giantship is gone somewhat crestfallen,⟦br⟧
Stalking with less <qex>unconscionable</qex> strides.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not guided by, or conformed to, conscience; that
cannot be done in good conscience; <as>as, <ex>unconscionable</ex>
profits</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ungenerous as well as <qex>unconscionable</qex> practices.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un*con"scion*a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Un*con"scion*a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>unconscious</ent>⟦br⟧
